2.3 SVM Actions
---------------

The action type is specified using a unit16 at the beginning of each action 
following the file header.
Every action except the special META_NULL_ACTION begins with a VersionCompat 
object.

2.3.1 Control Action Types
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - 

2.3.1.1 META_COMMENT_ACTION (512)

A comment action has no effect on the rendering.
It contains the following parts :
string          comment
uint32          value
string          comment2


comment         The comment text

value           ... FIXME

comment2        ... FIXME

2.3.1.2 META_NULL_ACTION (0)

This action should never occur, ever.
It contains a uint16 that is never used.


2.3.2 Object Action Types
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - 

2.3.2.1 META_MAPMODE_ACTION (137)

This action loads a new MapMode object.
It therefore contains only a MapMode object.

2.3.2.2 META_TEXTLANGUAGE_ACTION (150)

This action sets the current text language.
It contains the following part :
uint16          languageType

languageType    It is a decimal code that specifies the language.
It is described in i18npool/inc/i18npool/lang.h

2.3.3 Drawing Action Types
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - 

2.3.3.1 META_LINECOLOR_ACTION (132)

A line color sets the pen color in the current context.
It contains the following parts
uint32          colorData
bool            isSet

colorData       The color of the pen, in RGB format         (... QColor::fromRgb format)
isSet           Should the color be applied (true), or should the pen be hidden (false)

2.3.3.2 META_FILLCOLOR_ACTION (133)

A fill color sets the brush color in the current context.
It contains the following parts
uint32          colorData
bool            isSet

colorData       The color of the brush, in RGB format         (... QColor::fromRgb format)
isSet           Should the color be applied (true), or should the brush be hidden (false)

2.3.3.3 META_POLYLINE_ACTION (109)

A polyline action draws a polygon (it does not fill it).

It contains the following parts
Polygon         polygon
    If the version of the action is greater than 1
PenInformations penInfos
    If the version of the action is greater than 2
bool            polygonFlags
    If polygonFlags is true
VersionCompat   flagsVersionCompat
Polygon         polygon (replaces the previous polygon)
bool            polygonFlagsEnabled
    If polygonFlagsEnabled
....... FIXME!

polygon         The polygon to draw
penInfos        The pen style to apply
polygonFlags    Indicate the presence of extra polygon informations
....... FIXME: next part is complicated...


